Mapa do Turismo Brasileiro -- Dataset
======================================

SOURCE
------

Portaria MTUR no 9, de 24 de abril de 2025
URL: https://www.mapa.turismo.gov.br/mapa/init.html
Issued by: Ministerio do Turismo (MTur), Brazil
License: Federal government open data (CC-BY / public domain for federal publications)


CURRENT FILES
-------------

municipios_mtur_2024.csv
    16-row sample (BA/RJ/SP) for offline testing and CI fallback.
    Do NOT delete -- used by the full test suite when no 2025 file is present.

municipios_mtur_2025.csv
    NOT INCLUDED -- must be downloaded by the operator (see steps below).
    Once present, MturClient._load_csv() automatically uses it (newest filename wins).


HOW TO DOWNLOAD THE 2025 DATASET
---------------------------------

1. Go to: https://www.mapa.turismo.gov.br/mapa/init.html

2. Click "Municipio Categorizado Detalhado Excel"

3. Select:
     Ano (year):        2025
     Macrorregiao:      Todas (All)
     UF:                Todas (All)

4. Click Download -- the portal saves an XLSX file to your Downloads folder.

5. Convert to CSV:
     python scripts/mtur_xlsx_to_csv.py <path/to/downloaded.xlsx>

   This writes:  data/mtur/municipios_mtur_2025.csv

   Optional dry-run (print first 5 rows without writing):
     python scripts/mtur_xlsx_to_csv.py <path/to/downloaded.xlsx> --dry-run

   Requires openpyxl (operator-only install, not a production dependency):
     pip install openpyxl


CSV SCHEMA
----------

  co_municipio,no_municipio,sg_uf,categoria,no_regiao_turistica

  co_municipio        7-digit IBGE municipality code (e.g. 2927408)
  no_municipio        Municipality name (e.g. Porto Seguro)
  sg_uf               2-letter state code (e.g. BA)
  categoria           MTur category string (raw; _map_categoria in mtur.py normalizes it)
  no_regiao_turistica Tourism region name (e.g. Costa do Descobrimento)

The converter script (scripts/mtur_xlsx_to_csv.py) uses a COLUMN_CANDIDATES map with
fallbacks for known header-name variants across portal releases, so minor column renames
in the XLSX do not break the conversion.


LOADER BEHAVIOR
---------------

MturClient._load_csv() (brave/clients/mtur.py) globs data/mtur/municipios_mtur_*.csv
sorted descending by filename. The newest filename wins automatically:

  municipios_mtur_2025.csv  <-- used when present (highest sort order)
  municipios_mtur_2024.csv  <-- fallback for CI / offline tests

No code change is needed after placing the 2025 CSV -- the loader picks it up on the
next MturClient.fetch_municipalities() call.


2025 CATEGORY NOMENCLATURE
---------------------------

Portaria 9/2025 introduced new category names. _map_categoria in brave/clients/mtur.py
handles both old and new nomenclature:

  Old: A, B  ->  New: "Municipios turisticos"       ->  Norteia: "Oferta Principal"
  Old: C, D  ->  New: "com oferta turistica complementar"  ->  Norteia: "Complementar"
  Old: E     ->  New: "de apoio ao turismo"          ->  Norteia: "Apoio"

Raw category strings from the XLSX are stored as-is; the mapping happens at read time.
